</p>

<p>The tone of your message should be gentle and understanding, avoiding clichés or minimizing the depth of their loss.  Focus on offering support and remembering the positive impact the pet had on their life.  Avoid offering unsolicited advice or comparisons to other losses; simply being present and offering comfort is often the most meaningful gesture.  Remember to keep the message concise and sincere, focusing on the positive memories associated with the pet.</p>
    

